  "learn": {
    "heading": "What is a ratio?",
    "intro": "<p>A <strong>ratio</strong> compares two amounts. We can write it with the word <em>to</em>, with a colon, or as a fraction. To build one, you just count each group.</p>",
    "examples": [
      "<strong>2 cats and 3 dogs</strong> → the ratio of cats to dogs is <strong>2 to 3</strong>, or <strong>2:3</strong>.",
      "Order matters: cats to dogs is 2:3, but dogs to cats is <strong>3:2</strong>."
    ]
  },
